       RELAXATION VOICEOVER INSTRUCTIONS
-----------------------------------

Hi. Thanks for completing that questionnaire.

The next part of the experiment is a relaxing
meditation exercise. I'd like you to take your hands off the
computer mouse and keyboard, and pick up the seashell that we've placed 
on the desk just behind your screen, on the right-hand side.  Can you see it?  If you have any trouble finding it, please
raise your hand and an experiment administrator will come to help.

Now, with the seashell in your hand, please sit back in your seat and close your
eyes, leaving your arms resting at your sides. I'll let you know when it's time to re-open your eyes and move
on to the next phase of the experiment. For now, just take a deep
breath and leave behind any concerns that might have been on your
mind before.

With your eyes closed, think of a relaxing place on a beach where
you would like to be.  Imagine that you are there at the beach, and
you have some free time to just relax and let your mind wander over
pleasant thoughts while you listen to the sounds of the waves.



OK, you can open your eyes whenever you feel ready, and sit back up 
in your seat. Please place the seashell back where you found it, for the next person to use.
Once you click continue, you'll
see on the screen some instructions for the next phase of the
experiment. Please read them and let the experiment administrator
know if you have any questions."
